There was a time when children only needed to master reading, writing and arithmetic, yet a new toy wants to teach them how to program a computer - and it's aimed at four- to seven-year-olds.

Called Primo, the kit comes with a wooden robot called Cubetto, a programming board and instruction blocks.

Children place each of the instruction blocks onto the board in a set order to determine how Cubetto moves, before pressing a red button to set the robot in motion.

